snippet.textDisplay:
It looks nice now, but the Lakers (lack of significant) depth is likely to bite their asses, and bite hard.
Key Q: why is LBJ * still * playing top-10 minutes league-wide ...at age 35? He gooched-out from overuseage LAST season, and now you want to have him play just as many minutes WHILE ALSO playing the point?
This is not a good setup for success, as they instantly become a mediocre team any time that AD or LBJ are out. This is insane, really.


The Mavs weak point, apart from the obvious inexperience - is that they are too nice.

To get to the next tier they will need not only more playoff seasoning, but also that ENFORCER (and taunting/clowning) role-player. It won't be KP and something tells me it ain't Boban, either :)
